# =============================================================================
# Environment files — POLICY
# =============================================================================
# `.env`        — COMMITTED. Default config that's the same for everyone
#                 (non-secret defaults: app name, public URLs, feature flags).
# `.env.local`  — NOT COMMITTED. Per-developer overrides on top of `.env`
#                 (database password, API keys, anything secret or personal).
#
# `.env.<environment>` (`.env.development`, `.env.production`, …) — committed
# `.env.<environment>.local` (`.env.development.local`, …) — not committed
#
# This mirrors the convention Vite, Next.js, Create-React-App, and most
# modern frameworks use. If you put a secret in `.env`, it ends up in the
# repo. Use `.env.local` for anything you wouldn't paste in chat.
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

